summary: Completed frontend testing of CapCut-style video editor app. Dashboard and UI components work correctly, but project creation fails in browser mode due to missing Electron APIs.

ui_bugs.issue: Project creation fails silently in browser mode - 'Erstellen' button clicks but editor doesn't load

integration_issues.issue: App designed for Electron but running in browser mode - missing electronAPI causes project creation to fail

design_issues.issue: Modal overlay intercepts pointer events, requiring force=True for button clicks

passed_tests: Dashboard loads correctly with 'Neues Projekt erstellen' button
Project creation modal opens when clicking the button
Modal shows project name input, resolution dropdown (720p, 1080p, 4K), and FPS options (24, 25, 30, 60)
UI components are visually correct and responsive
Modal can be closed with 'Abbrechen' button
action_item_for_main_agent: CRITICAL: Fix project creation workflow - app is designed for Electron but running in browser mode. Either implement proper browser fallbacks for project creation or ensure app runs in Electron environment. The electronAPI is missing, causing project creation to fail silently after clicking 'Erstellen' button.

success_percentage.frontend: 40% - Dashboard and UI work, but core project creation fails
